commit_message: web: add link to github repo
web: add a link to github issue when a man page isn't found
readme: explain a bit more how explainshell works
license explainshell under the GPL (fixes #3)
web: serve css/js from cdnjs
web: add a new template for missing man page
options: catch shlex parsing errors
web/views: render error page on parsing error
web/index: focus search box on load (fixes #8)

web/es.js: add delay for highlight hover

Hover will now wait 250ms before activating all links, this should
provide a smoother behaviour when switching between the different
highlights.
web: disable autocapitalize and autocorrect in input field (fixes #12)

introduce a new parser

This parser is part of the sarge[1] package. It's capable of understanding
things like pipelines, redirections, lists (;, &, &&, ||) and compound
commands. Supporting command substitutions will be added later on.

The parser is based on a partial rewrite of shlex, and a fairly simplistic
recursive parser.

1: https://bitbucket.org/vinay.sajip/sarge

commit_message: fix various pyflakes warnings
algo/features: delete unused code
matcher: don't fail matching when a manpage isn't found

matcher: visit pipe nodes

We add a matchresult for each pipe and take the help text
from hand picked strings taken from bash(1).
matcher: visit operator nodes
matcher: visit redirection nodes
matcher: visit compound nodes
test-matcher: add a test for nested subshells

web/explain: pass all of the matcher's matchgroups to the explain template

The idea is to send each group to the template, and let the user navigate
between groups with a prev/next button. Each time, a certain group will be
displayed, with the 'shell' group being the first. So when the page loads,
the user is going to see explanations of shell syntax, and clicking the next
button will move to the first group of command explanations.

Suppose we have the command 'a | b', then first we're going to see what '|'
means, then clicking next will show what 'a' means, and another click will show
what 'b' means.

We might want to show everything in case there are <5 (or something like that)
lines.
web/es.js: move some logic from explain.html to es.js
es.js: when emptying the canvas, also clear all event handlers
es.js: maintain a linked list of command groups for navigation
web/explain: allow navigating the groups
web: set the font of the unknown circle's question mark

web/explain: adjust command font-size with respect to its length

Far from perfect but should get the job done for most longish commands, and it
doesn't add a dependency on some jQuery plugin that does a lot of magic.

Maybe we can add a scroll or '...' for longer ones in the future.
web/explain: give more room for margin when adjusting font size
web/templates: add missing closing </form>
web/explain: correctly set prev/next button text
web: add font-awesome for local dev
es.js: explicitly pass the group to clear()

web/explain: connect matches with the same help text to a single box

Previously we displayed multiple help boxes for (non adjacent) boxes, because
only adjacent matches were merged. This changes that so all matches that share
the same help text will connect to the same box, and thus help boxes with the
same text will not be duplicated.

For now, lines simply cross one another, but we might want to add a visual to
make it clearer when they meet, such as dotting, or a half circle.

es.js: don't set the canvas height if there's no help text for the current group

This can happen when multiple simple commands are involved and the current
command wasn't found.

errors: correctly handle ParsingError init at eof

When the error is at the EOF.
es.js: restore behavior when displaying command synopsis
views: extract explaincommand from explain function
views: extract explainprogram from explain

web: change url format to /explain?cmd=... (fixes #7)

Now that we support complex commands, it no longer makes sense to have urls of
the form '/explain/<prog>..' since a command might involve multiple programs.

Instead, we change the url format the more simplistic form of /explain?cmd=,
which should also make it easier to consume and doesn't require manipulating
the query, like we used to do with client code.

The old url will remain for now.
web/explain: fix links to alternative man pages

store: remove optional section parameter to findmanpage

Instead, the query is made up of <name>[.<section>], so everything
after the last dot from the right, is taken as the section.
call alternative man pages "suggestions" (was "others")
web/index: fix links

matcher: encode input in latin1 with replace

Our tokenizer chokes on non-latin1 characters, so replace
those until we get that sorted out.
es.js: remove unused function

es.js: document how we draw the lines

Before I forget (again) how it works..

update todo
web: update examples with shell syntax we support now

es.js: be more strict when shrinking command font size

This isn't robust as I had hoped, it needs to be automatic.
matcher: add specific help text for the various redirections
web/index: update note about missing features
es.js: don't reorder the same help boxes twice (will revert the first)

es.js: show all lines by default with the navigation buttons

Unless there's no shell syntax.
es.js: fix canvas height setting
web/explain: move navigation logic to es.js
config: change logging handler to FileHandler, let logrotate do its thing

views: trim command to 1000 characters

Don't make the parser work so hard for stupidly long (and malformed) commands.

web/explain: rework the connection between the command and help

The previous behaviour associated different parts of a group with the same help
id to prevent duplication of help boxes. But then it was possible for a single
command to span two groups, e.g. 'a -b && a -c' which would result in two
groups, but the second group would consist of only '-c'. This would mess up the
navigation because the second group would not show anything for the second 'a'.

Now each group is given a different name, so the first 'a' would be command0,
and the second would be command1, but we keep a reference for each span to its
help <pre> and handle it accordingly.

es.js: always connect the command name to its synopsis

It's too much trouble not to due to the rearrangement of help boxes.
es.js: omit group if it's full of unknowns
es.js: omit navigation if there's just a single group
macros: remove unused getargs argument
web/explain: refactor span class printing to a macro
web/views: remove unused param to the template
es.js: do some preprocessing on #command unknowns
es.js: make a missing man page clickable in #command
web/views: we only expect a missing man page error in explainold
update readme

es.js: fix an issue when moving between groups

When moving groups we hide/show some help boxes which may cause the page height
to shrink. This caused an issue when redrawing the lines and a misclaculating
the top of the canvas.

This is triggerable for example with the cut.. example, scrolling down a bit
and then moving to the next group.
matcher: identify arguments with no space at the end of short options (fixes #23)
views: add a warn log when parsing fails

matcher: don't assume the first node in a command is a WordNode

Previously we took the first node of a CommandNode and treated it as the
command name, but it's possible for it to be something else (e.g. a RedirectNode).

Now we look for the first node that is a WordNode.
views: log command string that caused uncaught exceptions to ease debugging
matcher: reset current option when fuzzy matching short options (fixes #14)

commit_message:
store: utf8 encode synopsis

We already encode the paragraph's text, and leaving this in Unicode caused
an annoying UnicodeWarning in matcher.py:312.
views: check for an empty query

parser: correctly increment position counter when seeing quotes

We need to increment the counter by 2, one for the opening quote and one for
the closing quote. This behaved correctly before if the next character after
the closing quote wasn't a control character.
web/explain: bind left/right arrows to navigate between groups (fixes #50)
matcher: print all matches in debugmatch
store: add support for nested commands
matcher: add support for nested commands (fixes #18)
matcher: add support for nesting through flags
matcher: add support for ending a nested command with an argument

commit_message:
parser: allow visiting the end of a simple command

The return value of visitcommand is passed into visitcommandend. This makes it
easier to assosciate the two.
es.js: fix initialize to work with multiple commands and no shell groups
views/debug: allow editing the nestedcommand field
matcher: don't fail prematurely if a partialmatch is unsuccessful
views: strip the command

matcher: pass unicode into findmanpage

mongo complains when you pass it invalid utf8, so simply pass it a vaild
unicode string.

views/explain: pass unicode to the templater

We convert what the user passes in to Latin1 (while replacing), but Jinja
expects Unicode when dealing with strings, so convert it back to Unicode after
we finish processing.

matcher: fix handling of arguments following an --x=y option (fixes #68)

When seeing an option of the form --x=y, the matcher would also consider
subsequent arguments to also be a possible argument to the --x option. We now
reset the current option when seeing '='.
manager: change inputs to be paths to gz files (or dirs)
web: fix another unicode issue when rendering errors

views/explain: merge lines going to the same help box

Instead of drawing multiple lines for repeated options, we connect them near
the top.

web/explain: don't reverse the order of left going lines (fixes #35)

Although visually pleasing, having the help boxes appear in left-to-right order
is more intuitive than reversing them for the sake of not having the lines
cross each other.

es.js: assign each group a constant color for the lines once the page loads

Previously, it was shuffled everytime drawgrouplines was called (e.g. via
resize()).
es.js: remember the last commandselector so we don't have to pass it into clear

es.js: allow passing options into drawgrouplines

In a future change we'd like to control whether we hide the current group help
boxes or not.
es.js: add a function to get all associated spans in #command

web/explain: stick the command to the top when scrolling (fixes #54)

We use Bootstrap's Affix plugin to fix #command to the top of the page when
scrolling. Lines are drawn only for the visible portions of the command.

es.js: simplify inview

We only really care (for now) that the middle of the given element
is inside the viewport. No need to compute the ratio.

web/explain: pass mouse events from the canvas to the underlying element

When scrolling, our stack order is:

1) canvas
2) command bar at the top
3) help table

This causes hovering in the help table to not work. 'pointer-events' is used
to delegate events to the help table.
web/explain: use a class for the help boxes
es.js: pass optional elements into optionsselector
es.js: use a different background for help boxes of a command start
matcher: pop all groups that are created as a result of argument nesting

web/views: some commands have no synopsis

lexgrog sometimes fails to extract the synopsis of a command (seen with
swapoff.8).

es.js: ignore unknown spans when coloring synopsis boxes

This caused spans to be mistakenly taken as .simplecommands, which made help
boxes use the wrong class.

es.js: temporarily disable unknown lines going up

The canvas used to start a little above #command, which left some room for
lines to go up. Since the command is fixed to the top, there's no room right
now so disable this behavior until that gets sorted out.

es.js: fix location of one of the lines

Not really noticable...
parser: rename function parameter for clarity
parser: remove unnecessary lambda

parser: remove unused function parse_redirection_input

Apparently this was never called and already handled in parse_redirections1.
parser: add support for <& redirections

parser: don't choke on invalid use of shell redirection

Malformed commands such as 'ssh.. <user>@<pass>' would confuse the parser
because of a missing target for the last output redirection. These are quite
popular in examples, so it's unfortunate we can't display something more
meaningful than an error.

(bash errors out with a similar message to ours)

matcher: switch over to bashlex for parsing (fixes #24)

bashlex is a port of GNU bash parser and supports more complicated constructs
such as process/command substitutions, variables, control flows and more.

We don't actually visit those new nodes just yet. First, make sure the existing
functionality is working.
matcher: simplify _markunparsedunknown
matcher: decode back from latin1 in the matcher rather than views

matcher: add support for command substitutions (fixes #24)

to keep things simple in the UI, we only add a link to /explain?cmd= with the
contents of the substitution (for now)

commit_message:
explain: don't allow newlines in the input

explainshell doesn't support multiline commands
views: catch NotImplementedError that bashlex might throw
matcher: add support for variable assignments (fixes #103)
es.js: show lines for unknowns when explaining shell only
tests: fix while/for semicolon matching

matcher: limit the recursive parsing to 1

we don't use anything beyond that in the UI anyway
matcher: visit expansions in the word after the for loop 'in' keyword

views: put the substitution links in spans

to make them easier to select in es.js
index: add examples for the new constructs
about: update
views: include the missing feature on NotImplementedError
helpconstants: add paragraph explaining += in assignments
matcher: add support for function definitions (fixes #81)
matcher: consider { } part of the function definition

matcher: remember defined functions and match accordingly (fixes #81)

we keep track of which functions are defined and try to match commands against
them before looking up a manpage.

this trick makes the results for the forkbomb make some sense ;)
index: use a macro for generating examples html
helpconstants: improve english

matcher: explain comments (fixes #104)

the AST has no nodes comments since those are ignored by bashlex, but we can
use a trick and find it ourselves by looking if it's beyond the end.
matcher: handle input consisting of solely a comment
matcher: use a namedtuple to describe expansions

commit_message: es.js: lots of linting fixes, thanks jshint!
manpage: don't change the environment directly

matcher: run bashlex in non strictmode

so things like missing heredocs don't raise an error

matcher, es.js: explain shell expansions such as ~, $@ (fixes #55)

These are displayed differently in the UI. Instead of using the usual help box
with a line connected to it, we display a popover when hovering over an
expansion. Also, color them in red and write something at the top of the page
so people notice.

The reason we don't reuse the existing logic for displaying them is that right
now the UI isn't really suited for nested explanations, so in the following
command:

$ echo "a $1"

the word "a $1" is an argument of echo and has its own help box, but if we
wanted to give $1 one too it would somehow have to overlap the outer one. It's
doable but too complicated, and I'm quite happy with this alternative.

views: add nbsp instead of spaces inside words

for some reason this messes things up if two popovers are adjacent, e.g.

echo "$1 $2"

and trying to hover $1

matcher: correctly check for digits in parameter node

It would not enter the if when int(value) == 0, and would
then fail on referencing the undefined kind variable.

explain: don't escape the command start, formatmatch already does (fixes #110)

This would escape the text twice, which would cause a mess if the text
contains html due to expansions or other added html by views.py.

matcher: ensure that the program part of a command isn't marked as unknown

If a man page has no synopsis, it could be mistaken to be an unknown part
of the command, even though we have a matching man page. So workaround that
by setting a default 'no synopsis found' so everything else works as expected.

Maybe we're better off with not including these man pages in the db at all?
They might still contain options, but the one I've seen (puppet) doesn't and
I don't feel like messing with that right now.
add some inline documentation
add man pages for a couple shell builtins (fixes #115, #124)
store: special case '.' when looking up a man page

errors: don't ask people to tell me a man page is missing

I don't have the capacity to add these one by one. It only makes sense if
someone has a dump of a few hundred or more that aren't in the db for
some reason.

web/explain: set top search box value from the url

Thanks to Justin Winokur for the report.
web/explain: replace + with a space when setting search box value
readme: update that we're using bashlex
web/explain: replace spaces before decoding the param so + is correctly preserved
requirements: anchor packages to avoid potential issues with new versions
tools/extractgzlist: fix typo: $secion -> $section

vagrant: add shell provisioner

This allows a local server to be built/started with:

    vagrant up
    vagrant ssh -c "cd /vagrant && make serve"

README.md: set PYTHONPATH in manager.py example

This avoids the following error:

    vagrant@precise64:/vagrant$ python explainshell/manager.py --log info manpages/1/echo.1.gz
    Traceback (most recent call last):
      File "explainshell/manager.py", line 3, in <module>
        from explainshell import options, store, fixer, manpage, errors, util, config
    ImportError: No module named explainshell
    vagrant@precise64:/vagrant$

Resolves https://github.com/idank/explainshell/pull/140

es.css/a: tweak down S&L to 3:1 contrast (fixes #38)

The original color, #66a3ff, has a contrast against white of 2.5:1 which is
even smaller than WCAG 2.0 contrast on large text/icons (3:1). This commit
decreases H to ~220 and L to ~165, and provides this value.

As a reference, H~225 and L~144 gives contrast = 3.9:1, close to the 4.5:1
recommended minimum. I'm not going that far, since a change so big means
redrawing the site LOGO.
manpage: set encoding to utf8 when generating man pages (fixes #141, #142)
requirements: readd bashlex that was mistakenly removed in 0c8986e
ui/index: advertise showthedocs.com

requirements: upgrade nltk to 2.0.5

See https://github.com/nltk/nltk/issues/824.
docker: add Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml and how to use it
readme: better highlighting of shell commands for github
readme: fix docker instructions

vagrant: improve the experience

* add wildcard bind for runserver
* auto start server in vagrant
* auto add grep.1.gz
* change port forward in vagrant

web/ui: implement text parts of logo using css (issue #155)

The logo currently has white pixels in the background, which makes implementing
a dark theme difficult.

This work would also allow us to change the black parts of the logo to
something more readable once the "dark" theme is active.

web/ui: assign colors in circular fashion for command links

For queries that require a lot of links to a point where we run out of the
array.  When we use one color we will push it back to the end of the colors
queue.

web/views: properly escape nested commands

This fixes problems with e.g. `awk <&3`.
web/views: add test for the link generation of a nested command
web/ui: rename logo.png to shell.png to avoid cache hit loading the old one

readme: fix header formatting

The first line was presumably supposed to be a markdown header,
but was missing a space after the `#`.  Also, renders a bit large to
as a level-1 header, so make it a level-2 header.
templates: adjust fonts url to be ssl compatible (issue #135)

add a misc directory

has a bunch of config files from a production server
index: drop the "new" div
requirements: sync with latest
dockerfile: unify RUN commands with shell '&&'

web/ui: rename canvastop to canvasTop

I could never stop reading it as canvaStop so to make it easy for the eye.
web/ui: remove unneccessary calls to jQuery

web/ui: rename a few variables for clarity

Rename rr to commandRect and commandrect to commandWrapperRect to avoid
variable commandrect and commandRect.
web/ui: introduce starty to each link
web/ui: use same pattern to create SVG path
web/ui: two links use the same line when pointing to the same help

web/ui: added theme support for the website

The user selects a theme using a dropdown near the menu and their preference is
saved in localStorage.

There are two themes available: the default, white background one and a dark
theme.

web/ui: setting theme server side to prevent flashing (fixes #227)

Use a cookie to save the chosen theme and render it server side into the
generated html.

Also renamed 'default' theme as Light consistent with other
implementations.
Adds a check to not load GA if the DNT header is sent
web/templates: remove google analytics
